Main Responsibilities:

  Supervise on-site installation works by company engineers and sub-contractors
  Ensure installation is carried out as per construction drawings
  Comply with the site works and safety rules and regulation 
  Walls and equipment setting out floor marking
  Steel structure erection and modular wall and ceiling installation
  Equipment M&amp;E hook-up and T&amp;C
  Coordinate material deliveries to the site
  Ensure site good housekeeping and safe working conditions
  Daily manpower and tools management

Requirements:

  10 years of construction site-related installation experience
  Supervise Construction Work for WSH (also known as BCSS)
  Work at Heights course
